<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Project>
  <!--
    Within-family exact-pin nuspec dependencies require external Version provisioning.

    The csproj shape declares:
      <PackageVersion Include="Janset.SDL2.{Role}.Native" Version="[$(Sdl<Major><Role>FamilyVersion)]" />
    where the family-version property defaults to $(Version), with a parseable
    "0.0.0-restore" sentinel as restore-safe fallback.

    MSBuild captures item metadata at static-evaluation time â€” BEFORE any target
    runs. MinVer sets $(Version) at target time. The two timings cannot be reconciled
    via a target that updates the PackageVersion item, because by GenerateNuspec the
    package dependency version is already resolved from project.assets.json (captured
    at restore time, BEFORE MinVer's targets are loaded by the package's own restore).

    Frontier confirmation (2026-04-16): no major .NET multi-package monorepo
    auto-derives within-family exact pin from MinVer for standalone `dotnet pack`.
    LibGit2Sharp hardcodes the literal version. SkiaSharp uses minimum range, not
    exact pin. SDL3-CS bundles natives. Avalonia uses minimum range with CPM. We are
    not implementing a half-broken hack; we accept the constraint and document it.

    Production path (Cake, Stream D-local):
      Cake determines the family version (MinVer-derived from git tag, or release-set
      lookup) and orchestrates pack via two MSBuild invocations: an explicit restore
      with the family version + `Version` + `MinVerSkip=true` properties, then a pack
      with the no-restore flag passing the same properties. Cake also pre-builds the
      .Native csproj with the same properties so the ProjectReference sub-build
      resolves to the matching version. The two-step ensures restore and pack see
      consistent values, restore writes [X.Y.Z] into project.assets.json, and pack
      emits the correct exact pin in the nuspec.

    Direct `dotnet pack` (developer convenience):
      Without explicit version properties, $(Version) is empty at static evaluation,
      Sdl<Major><Role>FamilyVersion falls through to "0.0.0-restore" (sentinel),
      and the nuspec emits "[0.0.0-restore]" as the within-family exact pin. This
      is wrong-on-purpose and SHOULD NEVER SHIP. The structural validator (PreFlight,
      A-risky step 3) checks csproj shape; the post-pack nuspec assertion (Stream
      D-local) catches the sentinel before publish.

    The guard target below escalates to a hard error during pack of a Janset.SDL2.*
    managed package when no version was provided externally. Native csprojs are
    payload-only and exempt (they ship just fine with MinVer's auto-derived version).
  -->
  <Target Name="_GuardAgainstShippingRestoreSentinel"
          BeforeTargets="GenerateNuspec"
          Condition="'$(IsPackable)' != 'false' and '$(PackageId.StartsWith(`Janset.SDL2.`))' == 'true' and '$(PackageId.EndsWith(`.Native`))' != 'true'">
    <Error Text="A-risky guard: Janset.SDL2.* managed pack invoked without explicit family version. Direct 'dotnet pack' would emit [0.0.0-restore] as the within-family exact pin â€” wrong-on-purpose sentinel. Run via Cake (Stream D-local), or pass -p:Sdl{Major}{Role}FamilyVersion=X.Y.Z -p:Version=X.Y.Z -p:MinVerSkip=true (and use a separate 'dotnet restore' step with the same properties). PackageId=$(PackageId), Version=$(Version), Sdl2CoreFamilyVersion=$(Sdl2CoreFamilyVersion), Sdl2ImageFamilyVersion=$(Sdl2ImageFamilyVersion), Sdl2MixerFamilyVersion=$(Sdl2MixerFamilyVersion), Sdl2TtfFamilyVersion=$(Sdl2TtfFamilyVersion), Sdl2GfxFamilyVersion=$(Sdl2GfxFamilyVersion). To bypass this guard for a deliberate sentinel pack (rare), pass -p:AllowSentinelExactPin=true."
           Condition="'$(AllowSentinelExactPin)' != 'true' and (
                      '$(Sdl2CoreFamilyVersion)'  == '0.0.0-restore' or
                      '$(Sdl2ImageFamilyVersion)' == '0.0.0-restore' or
                      '$(Sdl2MixerFamilyVersion)' == '0.0.0-restore' or
                      '$(Sdl2TtfFamilyVersion)'   == '0.0.0-restore' or
                      '$(Sdl2GfxFamilyVersion)'   == '0.0.0-restore')"/>
  </Target>
</Project>
